  "commentary": "With SPX at 6775.64 sitting below the GEX flip at 6795 in a PIN regime, dealers are currently net buyers of the selloff, providing support around the 6770 max negative gamma level where they'll aggressively buy dips. The thick positive gamma walls stacked above (6785-6800) create a natural magnet effect, with dealers expected to sell any rallies back toward 6795-6800 as they hedge their long gamma positions. Key levels to watch are 6770 downside support where dealer buying intensifies, and 6795-6800 resistance zone where dealer selling pressure kicks in.\n\nBottom line: expect the market to chop between 6770 and 6800 with a bias toward mean reversion back to 6790-6795.",
